node.text:
Pretty sure this is the first Apparel Co x Venture Capital collab in history. Definitely won't be our last. @776fund is proud to be working with @RowingBlazers to make our 1st merch drop EXCLUSIVELY for college athletes & in support of their mental health (thx to AAAD). All credit to @jackcarlson and his team for the awesome job on this super limited design.

We've already started putting dollars into supporting our founders via our 2% Growth & Caregiving Program—it's something I know I wish I had when I was a first-time CEO at 22 + clueless about how my mental health affected my output. 

Selected athletes will receive a special edition tee not available to the general public; a RB discount code they can share to raise money for AAAD; + opportunities for additional products + partial scholarships.

Not sure if you all on IG will wanna watch me demo software, but we just added the ability to Give Flowers (Give Thanks) within Cerebro. I wanted a way for anyone at @776fund to be able to record when someone does something kind for them. Why? Because it's really important to know who your allies are + find ways to do right by em. 💐💐💐

Imagine the social graph we will have in a decade when we know all the kindness that's been extended / received in our network. Take it from the guy who coined "Karma" on Reddit -- this is going to be very valuable for ‪7️⃣7️⃣6️⃣‬ and our founders. ‪#BuildInPublic‬

Yes, Venture Capitalists can believe in Karma.

node.text: My birthday is today, April 24, which is also Armenian Genocide Remembrance Day... One of my earliest childhood memories was being told on this day (maybe my 5th birthday?) that I had a tremendous responsibility to make the most out of the opportunity my family had sacrificed so much for. 🇦🇲🙏 That's why recognition is such a small act that means so much to us, especially Armenian-Americans who've watched every single President bow to Turkey and their propaganda of denial. No more.

node.title: Will the US finally recognize the #ArmenianGenocide !?

May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'TC Elektra Health targets new $3 75M round to help women navigate menopause Every woman will go through menopause some time during her life, but like many other femtech topics, this one is still not talked about as much as it should be. Seven. Seven. Six.'.

node.text: The telehealth revolution is here but women are still massively underserved. Shoutout to @katelin_cruse for spearheading our @776fund search for menopausal & premenopausal support. Check out @elektrahealth in @techcrunch ➡️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alexis Ohanian Sr. on August 10, 2021 tagging @acphenderson, @jversi, @elektrahealth, and @776fund. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'TC Elektra Health targets new $3 75M round to help women navigate menopause Every woman will go through menopause some time during her life, but like many other femtech topics, this one is still not talked about as much as it should be. Seven. Seven. Six.'.

Photo by Alexis Ohanian Sr. on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Elektra's platform offers clinical care via telemedicine and its proprietary "Meno-morphosis' program that features evidence-based guidance on symptoms, a community of support and access to 1:1 dedicated menopause expert. The program will open to the public in 2022 "We are all about caring for women by providing content, education, care, coaching and counseling, especially working in the arc of their journey." -Elektra Health Co-founder, Jannine Versi'.

Photo by Alexis Ohanian Sr. on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '" This is such an intimate topic, but we have referral rates of 40% where women are talking about it themselves and then bring a friend along. Sustaining that is important to us. We are seeing clusters of friends come along and really bond with the community. -Elektra Health Co-founder, Jannine Versi'.

Photo shared by Alexis Ohanian Sr. on August 10, 2021 tagging @katelin_cruse. May be an image of text that says 'Katelin Holloway, founding partner at Seven Seven Six, said in her previous roles leading compensation and benefits for companies, she became increasingly aware that the need for menopause care was just as desired by employees as fertility benefits. When her employees began requesting desk fans she started investigating the source of the requests and found it was from the company's z employees, and all women.'.

Photo by Alexis Ohanian Sr. on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '" Irealized had a decent cohort of women experiencing menopause. The fan on the desk was kind of a 'bat signal' to other employees, unlocking conversations between them where they had previously been experiencing these symptoms in silos. -Katelin Holloway'.

Photo by Alexis Ohanian Sr. on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Once Holloway became an investor, she put out the call again looking for a company providing that kind of care and was introduced to Elektra. She called Elektra's co-founders "incredible women who care deeply about this space and have amazing credentials and background to bring to this company." She was also sold on their approach of care, community and content, which aligns with what was working in the pregnancy and fertility spaces.'.

Pretty sure this is the first Apparel Co x Venture Capital collab in history. Definitely won't be our last. @776fund is proud to be working with @RowingBlazers to make our 1st merch drop EXCLUSIVELY for college athletes & in support of their mental health (thx to AAAD). All credit to @jackcarlson and his team for the awesome job on this super limited design.

We've already started putting dollars into supporting our founders via our 2% Growth & Caregiving Program—it's something I know I wish I had when I was a first-time CEO at 22 + clueless about how my mental health affected my output. 

Selected athletes will receive a special edition tee not available to the general public; a RB discount code they can share to raise money for AAAD; + opportunities for additional products + partial scholarships.
Leaked footage of how I do all my investing for #NFTs and @776fund 🧐 @olympiaohanian
